43_is_now_available"},{"short_id":"cvt7fd","created_at":"2026-03-20T05:21:12.000-05:00","title":"EnshittifAIcation","url":"https://it-notes.dragas.net/2026/03/20/enshittifaication/","score":35,"flags":1,"comment_count":14,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"draga79","user_is_author":true,"tags":["vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cvt7fd","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cvt7fd/enshittifaication"},{"short_id":"5qq9iv","created_at":"2026-03-20T04:57:55.000-05:00","title":"Raphtory: The temporal graph engine","url":"https://www.raphtory.com/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eSource code: \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/Pometry/Raphtory/\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://github.com/Pometry/Raphtory/\u003c/a\u003e\nHeard about from this explanation on computerphile: \u003ca href=\"https://youtu.be/ZP6Bh3iWklQ\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://youtu.be/ZP6Bh3iWklQ\u003c/a\u003e\nPaper: \u003ca href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2306.16309v2\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://arxiv.org/abs/2306.16309v2\u003c/a\u003e\nOfwhich the abstract:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRaphtory is a platform for building and analysing temporal networks. The library includes methods for creating networks from a variety of data sources; algorithms to explore their structure and evolution; and an extensible GraphQL server for deployment of applications built on top. Raphtory's core engine is built in Rust, for efficiency, with Python interfaces, for ease of use. Raphtory is developed by network scientists, with a background in Physics, Applied Mathematics, Engineering and Computer Science, for use across academia and industry.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n","description_plain":"Source code: https://github.com/Pometry/Raphtory/\r\nHeard about from this explanation on computerphile: https://youtu.be/ZP6Bh3iWklQ\r\nPaper: https://arxiv.org/abs/2306.16309v2\r\nOfwhich the abstract:\r\n\u003e Raphtory is a platform for building and analysing temporal networks. The library includes methods for creating networks from a variety of data sources; algorithms to explore their structure and evolution; and an extensible GraphQL server for deployment of applications built on top. Raphtory's core engine is built in Rust, for efficiency, with Python interfaces, for ease of use. Raphtory is developed by network scientists, with a background in Physics, Applied Mathematics, Engineering and Computer Science, for use across academia and industry.","submitter_user":"Arya","user_is_author":false,"tags":["databases","math"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/5qq9iv","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/5qq9iv/raphtory_temporal_graph_engine"},{"short_id":"4zl7y3","created_at":"2026-03-20T03:12:32.000-05:00","title":"Atuin v18.13 – better search, a PTY proxy, and AI for your shell","url":"https://blog.atuin.sh/atuin-v18-13/","score":5,"flags":1,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"msangi","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai","release"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/4zl7y3","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/4zl7y3/atuin_v18_13_better_search_pty_proxy_ai_for"},{"short_id":"1qcwfl","created_at":"2026-03-20T02:05:38.000-05:00","title":"Video Conferencing with Durable Streams","url":"https://s2.dev/blog/video-conferencing","score":7,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"infiniteregrets","user_is_author":true,"tags":["distributed","scaling"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/1qcwfl","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/1qcwfl/video_conferencing_with_durable_streams"},{"short_id":"bfhaih","created_at":"2026-03-20T00:42:43.000-05:00","title":"Minecraft Source Code is Interesting","url":"https://www.karanjanthe.me/posts/minecraft-source/","score":2,"flags":13,"comment_count":7,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"drmorr","user_is_author":false,"tags":["c++","games","performance"],"short_id_url":"